---
import BaseLayout from '@/components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import VerdictCardMock from '@/components/diagrams/VerdictCardMock.astro';
import AIFlow from '@/components/diagrams/AIFlow.astro';

const projects = [
  {
    slug: 'chatobd2',
    title: 'ChatOBD2',
    note: 'AI-native diagnostics, designed and engineered solo.',
    src: '/images/chatobd2/hero.webp',
    alt: 'ChatOBD2 marketing hero with phone mockup of a live diagnostic chat.',
    category: 'flagship',
  },
  {
    slug: 'magtek-platform',
    title: 'MagTek',
    note: 'Web experience across a multi-site platform on a long-running ASP.NET MVC stack.',
    src: '/images/magtek/homepage.webp',
    alt: 'MagTek homepage with metric story and team photography.',
    category: 'platform',
  },
  {
    slug: 'sawa',
    title: 'Sawa',
    note: 'Marketing site for an iMessage-native group dining app.',
    src: '/images/sawa/hero.webp',
    alt: 'Sawa marketing hero with phone mockup of a matched restaurant card.',
    category: 'product',
  },
  {
    slug: 'financial-platforms',
    title: 'Advisor portals',
    note: 'Multi-tenant frontend across 50+ wealth and banking institutions at InvestCloud.',
    src: '/images/financial-platforms/chase.webp',
    alt: 'Chase homepage built on the InvestCloud framework.',
    category: 'product',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Approach"
  description="How Moe Qadan approaches UX, frontend, design systems, AI-assisted prototyping, and platforms that already exist. Read the constraints first, pick the structure carefully, use AI where it earns its place."
  keywords={[
    'Moe Qadan',
    'design approach',
    'design engineering',
    'UX engineering',
    'frontend systems',
    'AI-assisted design',
    'prompt engineering',
    'design systems',
    'product design process',
  ]}
>
  <div class="apr">
    <div class="apr__atmos" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="apr__atmos-glow"></span>
    </div>

    <header class="apr__hero">
      <div class="container-site">
        <div class="apr__sxn">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">01</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">Approach</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-meta">A method, not a manifesto</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="apr__title">How I work.</h1>
        <p class="apr__subtitle">
          The short version. The long version is the rest of this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container-site apr__body">
      {/* Lead — discursive, not symmetrical */}
      <section class="apr__section apr__section--lead" data-reveal>
        <p class="apr__lead">
          A lot of the work I take on looks like repair. A platform that
          grew without a system. A site that ranks well and converts
          badly. A frontend that looks fine in Chrome and falls apart on
          iOS 15. Existing AI tooling that needs a real home in the
          codebase. Greenfield happens, but most of the work I do isn't
          that.
        </p>

        <p class="apr__para">
          I'm a senior generalist. UX, frontend, design systems, content
          architecture, SEO, performance, accessibility, AI-assisted
          prototyping. Whichever subset the work needs, on whatever
          platform the company runs on. The skills sit in one head, so
          the tradeoffs between them get made in one head.
        </p>
      </section>

      {/* What I actually do, day to day */}
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <header class="apr__sxn apr__sxn--inner">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">02</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">A normal week</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </header>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Concretely, the recurring work.</h2>

        <ul class="apr__bullets">
          <li>Modify a Razor partial that's used in fifty places, knowing the typed ViewModel will surface every consumer that needs to update.</li>
          <li>Argue for a slower header hero against the "but the carousel is what marketing wants" reflex, and sequence the migration so the analytics taxonomy doesn't go dark.</li>
          <li>Open a hand-authored CSS file, find the spacing token that's almost right but not quite, decide whether to add a new token or stretch the existing one. Most of the time it's stretch.</li>
          <li>Write a prompt module for ChatOBD2 that lives in the system, not in a component. Version it. Budget it inside the 38,000-token system prompt assembly.</li>
          <li>Read a Figma file someone handed off. Notice the spacing they almost got right. Translate it into production at fidelity, while quietly fixing the spacing.</li>
          <li>Run Lighthouse, watch the LCP regress when a marketing team drops a hero image, find a workable compromise that keeps both groups happy.</li>
          <li>Ship something into production that nobody but me will notice. Watch the bug board not light up.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      {/* AI in the work */}
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <header class="apr__sxn apr__sxn--inner">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">03</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">How AI actually fits in</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </header>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Two places: products, and the build.</h2>

        <p class="apr__para">
          The shape is the same in both: read the constraint, translate
          it into a prompt that lives in source, execute where the work
          fits best, ship reviewable output.
        </p>

        <div class="apr__flow" data-reveal>
          <AIFlow />
        </div>

        <p class="apr__para">
          <strong>In the products.</strong> ChatOBD2 is the worked
          example. Vehicle data flows through six deterministic
          reasoning layers before any model call. The system prompt
          isn't a string; it's a module that assembles fragments by
          priority inside a 38,000-token budget, keyed by verdict
          tier and code context. The fragments are typed, versioned,
          and reviewed in pull requests like any other source. A copy
          change is a one-file edit. The analytics taxonomy stays
          coherent because every fragment is tagged. Outputs are
          schema-bound, which means the rendering layer doesn't
          apologize for the model.
        </p>

        <p class="apr__para">
          <strong>The prompt practice.</strong> Prompts as production
          code. New behavior lands as a new fragment with a clear name.
          Failure modes are tested. Token budgets are tracked the way
          any other resource budget is. The result is AI you can keep
          iterating on, in the same review loop as the rest of the
          codebase.
        </p>

        <div class="apr__art" data-reveal>
          <span class="apr__art-caption">ChatOBD2 verdict surface</span>
          <VerdictCardMock />
        </div>

        <p class="apr__para">
          <strong>In the build.</strong> Claude and Cursor handle code
          work; the choice between them is contextual. Figma stays for
          precision and design-system maintenance. Claude Design comes
          in for visual exploration when a frame is faster to reason
          about than markup. The codebase is the source of truth across
          all of them.
        </p>

        <p class="apr__para">
          AI in the build, not the product. The model is one stage in a
          structured pipeline. A human owns every decision that ships.
          The goal is repeatability.
        </p>
      </section>

      {/* What I bring to a team */}
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <header class="apr__sxn apr__sxn--inner">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">04</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">What I'm best at on a team</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </header>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Where I land naturally.</h2>

        <ul class="apr__bullets">
          <li><strong>Owning the whole web experience for a team that doesn't have a department for it.</strong> One person carrying UX, the design system, the frontend, the content model, the SEO graph, and the performance budget.</li>
          <li><strong>Modernizing a platform that can't be rewritten.</strong> Long-running stacks have opinions. I read those first, plan around them, and ship in increments that don't require a flag day.</li>
          <li><strong>Building systems engineers actually use.</strong> Typed components. Tokens. Layout primitives. Real consumers from day one. No big-bang library that ships into a vacuum.</li>
          <li><strong>Sitting between design and engineering and unblocking both.</strong> I read intent, not just specs. Most production breakage lives in the gap a handoff doesn't see.</li>
          <li><strong>Building AI features as engineering.</strong> Prompt modules in source. Schema-bound outputs. Structured pipelines that hold up under traffic. ChatOBD2 is the worked example: six deterministic layers in front of every model call, prompts assembled per scan from a 38,000-token budget.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      {/* Tools */}
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <header class="apr__sxn apr__sxn--inner">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">05</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">Tools I reach for</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-meta">The judgment is the constant</span>
        </header>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">The default stack changes per project.</h2>
        <p class="apr__para">
          The judgment about which tool to use for which job stays the
          same.
        </p>

        <ul class="apr__tools">
          <li class="apr__tool">
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <header class="apr__tool-head">
              <span class="apr__tool-num">01</span>
              <span class="apr__tool-name">Claude</span>
            </header>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Code work and reasoning. The default for non-trivial refactors and anything that needs to think across more than one file.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="apr__tool">
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <header class="apr__tool-head">
              <span class="apr__tool-num">02</span>
              <span class="apr__tool-name">Cursor</span>
            </header>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Local iteration. Same code work as Claude, different interaction model. Whichever is faster on the task at hand.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="apr__tool">
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <header class="apr__tool-head">
              <span class="apr__tool-num">03</span>
              <span class="apr__tool-name">Figma</span>
            </header>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Precision design, component-system maintenance, handoff fidelity, and the occasional client review.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="apr__tool">
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="apr__tool-corner apr__tool-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <header class="apr__tool-head">
              <span class="apr__tool-num">04</span>
              <span class="apr__tool-name">Claude Design</span>
            </header>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Visual exploration when a frame is faster to think in than code. Output lands back in the codebase.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      {/* Across the work */}
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <header class="apr__sxn apr__sxn--inner">
          <span class="apr__sxn-num">06</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-label">Across the work</span>
          <span class="apr__sxn-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </header>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Different companies, different stacks, same question.</h2>
        <p class="apr__para">
          How do I move this surface from where it is to where it should
          be without breaking what's already running.
        </p>

        <div class="apr__work-grid">
          {projects.map(p => (
            <a
              href={`/work/${p.slug}`}
              class:list={['apr__work', `apr__work--${p.category}`]}
            >
              <span class="apr__work-corner apr__work-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="apr__work-corner apr__work-corner--tr" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="apr__work-corner apr__work-corner--bl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="apr__work-corner apr__work-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>

              <div class="apr__work-shot">
                <img
                  src={p.src}
                  alt={p.alt}
                  width="1440"
                  height="900"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
              </div>
              <div class="apr__work-meta">
                <h3 class="apr__work-title">{p.title}</h3>
                <p class="apr__work-note">{p.note}</p>
                <span class="apr__work-cta">
                  Case study
                  <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  </svg>
                </span>
              </div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Closing CTA */}
      <section class="apr__cta" data-reveal>
        <span class="apr__cta-corner apr__cta-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="apr__cta-corner apr__cta-corner--tr" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="apr__cta-corner apr__cta-corner--bl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="apr__cta-corner apr__cta-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="apr__cta-glow" aria-hidden="true"></span>

        <div class="apr__cta-text">
          <div class="apr__cta-eyebrow">
            <span class="apr__cta-dot"></span>
            <span>Get in touch</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="apr__cta-title">Working on something on the web?</h2>
          <p class="apr__cta-sub">
            Send a few sentences. Replies within a day.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="apr__cta-actions">
          <a href="/contact" class="apr__cta-primary">
            Send a message
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
          <a href="mailto:moe@qadan.co" class="apr__cta-ghost">moe@qadan.co</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .apr {
    position: relative;
  }

  .apr__atmos {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 600px;
    pointer-events: none;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .apr__atmos-glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: -180px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 1100px;
    height: 540px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 50% at 50% 50%, var(--color-accent-muted), transparent 70%);
    filter: blur(28px);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .apr__hero {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: calc(60px + var(--space-10));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .apr__hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }
  }

  /* Shared section-head pattern */
  .apr__sxn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .apr__sxn--inner {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .apr__sxn-num {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    height: 22px;
    padding: 0 7px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .apr__sxn-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .apr__sxn-rule {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-border), transparent);
    min-width: 32px;
  }

  .apr__sxn-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .apr__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(40px, 9vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .apr__subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .apr__body {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 1080px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .apr__body {
      padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .apr__section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .apr__section--lead {
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .apr__h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3.2vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 24ch;
  }

  .apr__lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .apr__para {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .apr__para strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .apr__bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 66ch;
  }

  .apr__bullets li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .apr__bullets li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 12px;
    height: 1px;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .apr__bullets strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .apr__art {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .apr__art-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .apr__art :global(.verdict-mock__head) {
    display: none;
  }

  .apr__art :global(.verdict-mock) {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .apr__flow {
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 var(--space-4);
  }

  /* Tools cards */
  .apr__tools {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .apr__tools {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }
  }

  .apr__tool {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-bg-elevated), var(--color-bg-muted));
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 280ms, transform 280ms var(--ease-out), box-shadow 280ms;
  }

  .apr__tool:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent-muted);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-hover);
  }

  .apr__tool-corner {
    position: absolute;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-text-subtle);
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0.4;
    transition: opacity 240ms, border-color 240ms;
  }

  .apr__tool-corner--tl { top: 8px; left: 8px; border-right: none; border-bottom: none; }
  .apr__tool-corner--br { bottom: 8px; right: 8px; border-left: none; border-top: none; }

  .apr__tool:hover .apr__tool-corner {
    opacity: 1;
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .apr__tool-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .apr__tool-num {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-bg-elevated), var(--color-bg-deep));
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .apr__tool-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .apr__tool-role {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Work grid — across-the-work */
  .apr__work-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .apr__work-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-6);
    }
  }

  .apr__work {
    --pc-accent: var(--color-accent);
    --pc-accent-rgb: var(--project-flagship-rgb);
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-bg-elevated), var(--color-bg-muted));
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
